A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Article 1 of Chapter 7 of Title 44 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated,
2 relating to landlord and tenant in general, so as to require landlords and managers of
3 apartment buildings or complexes to provide local police and fire departments certain
4 information; to provide for a penalty; to provide for an effective date and applicability; to
5 provide for related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
6 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
7 SECTION 1.
8 Article 1 of Chapter 7 of Title 44 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
9 landlord and tenant in general, is amended by adding a new Code section to read as follows:
10 "44-7-14.2.
11 (a) The landlord or manager of any apartment building or complex shall provide local
12 police and fire departments with current and up to date:
13 (1) After hours maintenance telephone numbers; and
14 (2) After hours management telephone numbers.
15 (b) Any landlord or manager found to be in violation of subsection (a) of this Code section
16 shall be fined $2,000.00 per violation.
