17 (c) Any landlord or manager found to be in continuing violation of subsection (a) of this
18 Code section shall be fined every five days they remain in violation.
19 (d) Any landlord or manager who receives a communication from local police and fire
20 departments shall respond to such communication within one hour. If the landlord or
21 manager does not respond, they shall be fined $5,000.00.
22 (e) All fines collected pursuant to this Code section shall be paid into Clayton County
23 Public Schools Homeless Education Department."
24 SECTION 2.
25 This Act shall become effective on July 1, 2025, and shall apply to all violations occurring
26 on or after such date.
27 SECTION 3.
28 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
